  "sourceQuote": "FarmingTracker.java: \"// timetracking.<rsprofile>.<regionID>.<VarbitID>=<varbitValue>:<unix time>\" ... String key = patch.configKey(); ... String value = strVarbit + \":\" + unixNow; configManager.setRSProfileConfiguration(TimeTrackingConfig.CONFIG_GROUP, key, value); | FarmingPatch.java: String configKey() { return region.getRegionID() + \".\" + varbit; } | TimeTrackingConfig.java: String CONFIG_GROUP = \"timetracking\";"
 },
 "notes": [
  "Coarse states derived from PatchImplementation.forVarbitValue(int) in RuneLite master (fetched 2026-07-19). Values not listed are unhandled (forVarbitValue returns null) and map to UNKNOWN.",
  "Produce.WEEDS entries (any weed stage, incl. high-value fallback weed ranges) are mapped to EMPTY: the patch needs raking/planting.",
  "RuneLite classifies the 'Check-health' stage of trees/bushes/fruit trees/etc. as CropState.GROWING at the final stage; per the task's coarse semantics (HARVESTABLE = fully grown / can check health) those values are mapped to HARVESTABLE here. Post-check 'Chop down' and 'stump [Clear]' values are CropState.HARVESTABLE in the source and stay HARVESTABLE.",
  "SPIRIT_TREE value 20 ('Spirit Tree[Travel,Talk-to,Inspect,Guide,Clear]', the fully grown usable tree) and value 44 ('Check-health') are CropState.GROWING in RuneLite but mapped to HARVESTABLE here as fully grown.",
  "FLOWER values 33-36 are a placed SCARECROW (not a crop); RuneLite classifies them GROWING. A scarecrow patch cannot be planted and never becomes harvestable.",
  "ANIMA plants have no diseased/dead CropState in RuneLite: each plant's single GROWING range includes its 'Withering' (2nd-to-last value) and 'Dead ... [Clear]' (last value) stages per the source comments (e.g. ATTAS 8-16: 15=withering, 16=dead). Anima plants are never harvestable.",
  "Growth: totalMinutes = tickrate * (stages - 1); Produce.stages counts states ('Typically tickcount+1' per source javadoc). Herb anchor holds: 20 min * 4 ticks = 80 min.",
  "TREE minimum is Oak (160 min); FRUIT_TREE all produce take 960 min; HERB all produce take 80 min.",
  "Farming ticks on Leagues worlds are 1 minute instead of 5 (FarmingTracker.isLeaguesWorld() divides tick rate by 5).",
  "The stored timestamp is only rewritten when the varbit changed or the stored value is >5 minutes old (FarmingTracker.updateData)."
 ]
